  "prompt": "Why didn't Balram (brother of Krishna) participate in the Mahabharat War?",
  "response": "Balram, the brother of Lord Krishna, chose not to participate in the Mahabharata War due to his stance on the conflict between the Pandavas and Kauravas. He had a strong belief in dharma (righteousness) and respected the principles of both sides. Balram was also a teacher of weapons and combat, and he felt a sense of loyalty to both families, as he had affection for both the Pandavas and the Kauravas.\n\nAdditionally, Balram's decision can be viewed as a way to maintain neutrality and avoid involvement in the fratricidal conflict. He believed that the war would lead to significant destruction and was averse to the bloodshed it would cause. Instead of taking sides, he opted to remain an observer, reflecting his wisdom and deep understanding of the moral complexities of the situation. By not participating in the war, Balram aimed to uphold his own ethical principles while also maintaining familial bonds.",
